{{Infobox sport tournament | name = 2002 Basque Pelota World Championships | image = 2002 Basque Pelota World Championships poster.png | caption = Tournament poster | location = {{flagicon|Spain}} [[Pamplona]], [[Spain]] | start_date = 21 | end_date = 31 August | administrator = [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]] | tournament_format = | venues = | teams = 16 | purse = | champions = {{flag|Spain}} | runners-up1 = {{flag|France}} | runners-up2 = {{flag|Mexico}} | matches = | points = | attendance = | previous = [[1998 Basque Pelota World Championships|1998]] | next = [[2006 Basque Pelota World Championships|2006]] | website = www.mundialnavarra2002.com }}
The '''2002 Basque Pelota World Championships''' were the 14th edition of the [[Basque Pelota World Championships]] organized by the [[International Federation of Basque Pelota|FIPV]].
==Participating nations== {{col-begin|width=70%}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Argentina}} *{{flag|Belgium}} *{{flag|Brazil}} *{{flag|Canada}} *{{flag|Chile}} *{{flag|Cuba}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Dominican Republic}} *{{flag|France}} *{{flag|Mexico}} *{{flag|Morocco}} *{{flag|Peru}} *{{flag|Philippines}} {{col-break}} *{{flag|Spain}} *{{flag|United States}} *{{flag|Uruguay}} *{{flag|Venezuela}} {{col-end}}
