{{infobox country at games | CGA = IVB | CGAname = [[British Virgin Islands Olympic Committee]] | games = Commonwealth Games | year = | flagcaption = [[Flag of the British Virgin Islands]] | oldcode = | website = {{url|bviolympics.org }} | location = | competitors = | sports = | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 1 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | app_begin_year = 1990 | app_end_year = | seealso = }} The [[British Virgin Islands]] have attended all seven [[Commonwealth Games]] since [[1990 Commonwealth Games|1990]].
Having first competed at Auckland in [[1990 Commonwealth Games|1990]], the British Virgin Islands had never won a medal of any colour at a Commonwealth Games until [[Kyron McMaster]] won the men's 400m hurdles at the [[2018 Commonwealth Games]] at [[Gold Coast, Queensland|Gold Coast]].<ref>{{cite news |author=Chris Scott |title=A year after Hurricane Irma, Kyron McMaster wins BVI's first Commonwealth medal |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/04/12/sport/kyron-mcmaster-wins-british-virgin-islands-first-commonwealth-medal/index.html |work=CNN |date=13 April 2017}}</ref> <ref name=":0">{{cite news |title=Kyron McMaster wins the British Virgins Islands’ first ever medal in perfect tribute to late coach |url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/sport/commonwealth-games/athletics/kyron-mcmaster-wins-the-british-virgins-islands-first-ever-medal-in-perfect-tribute-to-late-coach/news-story/b7ed98ce1326b89d80dcb22761c26977 |work=Herald Sun |date=13 April 2017}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news |title=Kyron McMaster overcomes adversity to create British Virgin Islands history |url=http://www.athleticsweekly.com/commonwealth/kyron-mcmaster-overcomes-adversity-to-create-british-virgin-islands-history-95287 |work=Athletics Weekly |date=13 April 2017}}</ref>
It was McMaster's first global title, having been disqualified from the 400m hurdles at the [[2017 IAAF World Championships|2017 IAAF World Athletics Championships]], though did go on to win the [[2017 IAAF Diamond League]] title the following month. <ref name=":0" />
