{{Infobox ski area |name= Silichy |logo= |picture= Silichy-02.jpg |caption= |location= [[Belarus]] |nearest_city= [[Lahojsk]] |coordinates = {{coord|54|08|54|N|27|50|05|E|type:landmark_scale:50000|display=inline}} |vertical= |top_elevation= |base_elevation= |skiable_area= 2.5 km (1.55 mi) |number_trails= |longest_run= |liftsystem= |lift_capacity= |terrainparks= |snowfall= |snowmaking= |nightskiing= |external_link= http://www.silichy.by/ |}}
'''Silichy''' or '''Silichi''' ({{lang-ru|Силичи}}, {{lang-be|Сілічы}}) is a [[ski resort]] situated in [[Lahojsk]] (or ''Logoysk''), [[Belarus]], located 30 km (18.64 mi) away from [[Minsk]].
Silichy was officially opened on January 29, 2005. The length of 3 routes for skiing is 2.5 km (1.55 mi), its total capacity is 1,000 skiers per day and it has a 4-chair elevator. There is a parking lot for 500 cars, hotel accommodation, and hire of skiing equipment.
The mountain skiing season starts in December and lasts until March (until there is no snow).<ref>{{en icon}} [http://www.radiobelarus.tvr.by/eng/textblock.asp?id=16&date=31.05.2006%209:43:00 Postcard from Belarus] Radiostation "Belarus", April 24, 2008</ref>
